when I do this I get the following error which I dont know how to fix: 

```
function expected at
  SMul (SpecialLinearGroup n R) (FixedDetMatrices n R m)
term has type
  Type (max u_2 u_1)
```
Would `FixedDetMatrix` not be more in line with other types?
Does this belong here?
I thought this was the natural place to put it since it where there are other results about S and T, but I'm happy to move it if you think there's a better file to put it in.
Hm, not sure why I thought it could go elsewhere. Never mind.

```suggestion
instance (m : R) : SMul (SpecialLinearGroup n R) (FixedDetMatrix n R m) where
  smul g A := g * A.1, by simp only [det_mul, SpecialLinearGroup.det_coe, A.2, one_mul]
```

```suggestion
lemma smul_def (m : R) (g : SpecialLinearGroup n R) (A : (FixedDetMatrix n R m)) :
    g  A = g * A.1, by simp only [det_mul, SpecialLinearGroup.det_coe, A.2, one_mul] :=
  rfl
```

```suggestion
instance (m : R) : MulAction (SpecialLinearGroup n R) (FixedDetMatrix n R m) where
  one_smul b := by rw [smul_def]; simp only [coe_one, one_mul, Subtype.coe_eta]
  mul_smul x y b := by simp_rw [smul_def,  mul_assoc, coe_mul]
```
I'm curious if there's a particular reason to make `m` explicit here.
Ah good point, fixed!
